Authorization is required
Your request has not been processed because it lacks valid authentication credentials.
What Causes a 401 Error?
• Invalid Credentials: The most common cause is incorrect login credentials. This could be due to a typo or outdated password.
• Session Timeout: If your session has expired, you might encounter this error.
• IP Address Blocking: Some websites block certain IP addresses, leading to a 401 error.
• Incorrect URL: Sometimes, the URL might be incorrect or the resource might have moved.
How to Fix a 401 Error?
• Check Credentials: Ensure that your username and password are correct.
• Clear Browser Cache: Sometimes, clearing your browser's cache can resolve the issue.
• Update URL: Make sure the URL is correct and hasn't changed.
• Contact Website Owner: If the problem persists, reach out to the website's support team for assistance.
